  "passageParts": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Given the advantages of electronic money, you might think that we would move quickly to the cashless society in which all payments are made electronically.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, a true cashless society is probably not around the corner. Indeed, predictions have been\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor two decades but have not yet come to fruition. For example, Business Week predicted in 1975 that electronic means of payment would soon “revolutionize the very\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof money itself,” only to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nitself several years later. Why has the movement to a cashless society been so\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nin coming?\n Although electronic means of payment may be more efficient than a payments system based on paper, several factors work\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe disappearance of the paper system. First, it is very\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nto set up the computer, card reader, and telecommunications networks necessary to make electronic money the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nform of payment. Second, paper checks have the advantage that they\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nreceipts, something that many consumers are unwilling to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​. Third, the use of paper checks gives consumers several days of “float” – it takes several days\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\na check is cashed and funds are\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfrom the issuer’s account, which means that the writer of the check can earn interest on the funds in the meantime.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 13
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nelectronic payments are immediate, they eliminate the float for the consumer.\n Fourth, electronic means of payment may\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nsecurity and privacy concerns. We often hear media reports that an unauthorized hacker has been able to access a computer database and to alter information\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthere. The fact that this is not an\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\noccurrence means that dishonest persons might be able to access bank accounts in electronic payments systems and\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfrom someone else’s accounts. The\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 18
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof this type of fraud is no easy task, and a new field of computer science is developing to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 19
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nsecurity issues. A further concern is that the use of electronic means of payment leaves an electronic\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthat contains a large amount of personal data. There are concerns that government, employers, and marketers might be able to access these data, thereby violating our privacy."
    }
  ],
